Okta Basics

Okta is an identity management service that's used in Labs to provide centralized authentication for Labs applications.

# 

<span key="602c0394dc954a2f906aa0b1e3d4c7f4"><span offset-key="602c0394dc954a2f906aa0b1e3d4c7f4:0">Okta Basics</span></span>

![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)

<span key="d53c25bc3f274d18b3df4418d0714df4"><span offset-key="d53c25bc3f274d18b3df4418d0714df4:0">Currently only Labs Managers have admin access to Okta administration. If you have Okta issues, please reach out to your Engineering Manager.</span></span>

<span key="6e9faafd00e04c4b80600cc846a63e23"><span offset-key="6e9faafd00e04c4b80600cc846a63e23:0">â€‹</span></span><a href="https://www.okta.com" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="8c6b9a4be6064acaa493016956fbe581" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-37214_259-37215-237__"><span data-key="d5f650e7282e457ca9ca51c0acde7aad"><span data-offset-key="d5f650e7282e457ca9ca51c0acde7aad:0">Okta</span></span></span></a><span key="2dbb1f66841d4c61b2c95df2e99c3760"><span offset-key="2dbb1f66841d4c61b2c95df2e99c3760:0"> is an identity management service that's used in Labs to provide centralized authentication for Labs applications.</span></span>

<span key="2d723a0f5c894846b5c1e63ac02c0033"><span offset-key="2d723a0f5c894846b5c1e63ac02c0033:0">We use a centralized identity management service because it is typically the way applications are authenticated in the industry. This gives our students practice using centralized identity management technologies like </span></span><a href="https://developer.okta.com/blog/2017/06/21/what-the-heck-is-oauth" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="74eb160833464defbb015d27ff34372e" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-37214_259-37215-237__"><span data-key="58065aa58b3d4728b41c8a3e22089107"><span data-offset-key="58065aa58b3d4728b41c8a3e22089107:0">OAuth</span></span></span></a><span key="705de1485d5c419896e987e52e7c96f8"><span offset-key="705de1485d5c419896e987e52e7c96f8:0"> and </span></span><a href="https://openid.net/connect/faq/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="2e98075f3a31460b85c8e37b63583cb6" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-37214_259-37215-237__"><span data-key="792cb38ca6d14ed989782d81a377bed4"><span data-offset-key="792cb38ca6d14ed989782d81a377bed4:0">OIDC</span></span></span></a><span key="26582ef7c23b4d109603bc452d2df87d"><span offset-key="26582ef7c23b4d109603bc452d2df87d:0">.</span></span>

<span key="76318af56eba467293f3ae99cdf0abe8"><span offset-key="76318af56eba467293f3ae99cdf0abe8:0">We use Okta specifically because it is an </span></span><a href="https://www.okta.com/resources/access-management-leader-gartner-magic-quadrant" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="795dd2873b6c4fc69149be3180ea6e29" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-37214_259-37215-237__"><span data-key="59869e64ee434e09b247e3c86c88d807"><span data-offset-key="59869e64ee434e09b247e3c86c88d807:0">industry leader</span></span></span></a><span key="7d467a072e1240b7b3175c1b1d397ade"><span offset-key="7d467a072e1240b7b3175c1b1d397ade:0"> and has high-quality support and documentation.</span></span>

<span key="caa37e094c5d4b6d9d44a1a21926863d"><span offset-key="caa37e094c5d4b6d9d44a1a21926863d:0">Here is a quick walk thru of okta and how it is used in our Labs projects.</span></span>

# 

<span key="7d3098d7f92d40e89a24079c99c7dde6"><span offset-key="7d3098d7f92d40e89a24079c99c7dde6:0">The Okta Account</span></span>

<span key="f177cfed279d4278bbef117a8f2cab6d"><span offset-key="f177cfed279d4278bbef117a8f2cab6d:0">Okta provides centralized identity management. This means that you can have a </span>*single*<span offset-key="f177cfed279d4278bbef117a8f2cab6d:2"> set of identities that can be used across many different applications. If you use Google services, you can see this in action as you log in to Google once but can move between Google apps (Mail, Calendar, Sheets, etc.) without having to log in each time.</span></span>

<span key="8f47348795fb4cb0af79563ef336746c"><span offset-key="8f47348795fb4cb0af79563ef336746c:0">We use Okta the same way. There is a </span>*single*<span offset-key="8f47348795fb4cb0af79563ef336746c:2"> Labs Okta account that has a set of identities that can access all Labs applications. These identities are test users that can be used by teams for testing their applications without having to constantly create new identities.</span></span>

<span key="43a20a2e5ca04c40aaf1e311b4d4b207"><span offset-key="43a20a2e5ca04c40aaf1e311b4d4b207:0">Since Labs applications are always under development, it's very handy to have a set of test identities readily available to test various aspects of your application.</span></span>

<span key="ad611bbee2f5429d8d727f8223080df4"><span offset-key="ad611bbee2f5429d8d727f8223080df4:0">Labs applications should </span>*always*<span offset-key="ad611bbee2f5429d8d727f8223080df4:2"> authenticate using the alias (auth.lambdalabs.dev), though, for reference, the Labs Organization URL is: </span></span><a href="https://dev-625244.okta.comdashboard" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="f33e2bf1cdcc42559af49cfa60ce40d1" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-37214_259-37215-237__"><span data-key="8ba3cb6f2ccd46b9876bf978861f5186"><span data-offset-key="8ba3cb6f2ccd46b9876bf978861f5186:0">https://dev-625244.okta.com</span></span></span></a><span key="f98e0d354b194f0c98c3448e6119c167"><span offset-key="f98e0d354b194f0c98c3448e6119c167:0">â€‹</span></span>

## 

<span key="91fa49e4cc154956803c3b2a60852463"><span offset-key="91fa49e4cc154956803c3b2a60852463:0">Retrieve Product Client ID</span></span>

<span key="156e615155644212812d5862700e70b3"><span offset-key="156e615155644212812d5862700e70b3:0">There is a single Client ID for each product that must be supplied to Labs project teams in order for them to enable authentication. Each product will be set up as an Okta Application. The Client ID can be found using the Admin interface, by clicking on the Applications Tab.</span></span>

<span key="68d17dddab0240bc979077c36f3c706e"><span offset-key="68d17dddab0240bc979077c36f3c706e:0">Products have </span>*one*<span offset-key="68d17dddab0240bc979077c36f3c706e:2"> client id that is </span>*shared*<span offset-key="68d17dddab0240bc979077c36f3c706e:4"> among all active projects working on that product. Client IDs should </span>*not*<span offset-key="68d17dddab0240bc979077c36f3c706e:6"> be shared across products.</span></span><span slate-void="true" key="acf6dc64948e423fabcef599b3dd5553"></span>

<span key="87b853412b1d4c32bc28ef8b3c47f981"><span offset-key="87b853412b1d4c32bc28ef8b3c47f981:0">Issuer URI</span></span>
